										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Branding job for 1Look DMB Agency.</p>
<p>The client didn&#8217;t wanted a distant change for the visual identity, specially regarding the orange curve and the &#8220;number 1&#8221;, then we had concluded that a modernization could do a better job.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>While redesigning, I have worked on a curved and more ludical way, but without going too far the old logo first-sight points (the orange curve and the number 1).</p>
<p><img class="alignnone img-responsive wp-image-459 aligncenter" src="./../../../../wp-content/uploads/2014/07/unnamed.jpg" alt="unnamed" width="300" /><br />
<img class="alignnone img-responsive wp-image-273 aligncenter" src="./../../../../wp-content/uploads/2016/07/599b05d5-eedd-4f32-bdad-9524cc1f2635.jpg" alt="599b05d5-eedd-4f32-bdad-9524cc1f2635" width="100%" srcset="./../../../../wp-content/uploads/2016/07/599b05d5-eedd-4f32-bdad-9524cc1f2635.jpg 1754w, ./../../../../wp-content/uploads/2016/07/599b05d5-eedd-4f32-bdad-9524cc1f2635-768x338.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1754px) 100vw, 1754px" /></p>
<p>After the logo redesigning, I made arts for a flyer and visit cards.</p>
<p>On the flyer, I made an illustration, which had been sketched before digital designing. It shows the importance of an present communication on our routine, where the advertising is everywere, in every shape and colors.</p>
